<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-06-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Caruth</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-06-25"><hi rend="italic">June 25,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>If you have not done so, ascertain at once whether it is agreeable to
                            Government of Portugal that our minister at Lisbon should act for
                            protection of Brazilian citizens in Portugal during suspension of
                            diplomatic relations between the two Governments.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>